description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have the passion to support our teams to deliver high quality compassionate care?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If the answer is yes, then this exciting opportunity to join our brand new Community Heart Failure Service in East Staffordshire as a Band 3 Administrator could be the perfect career move for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a conscientious individual with a can-do attitude and demonstrate a commitment to delivering high quality administration support. The successful applicant will have excellent communication and organisational skills and have a range of administration experience. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post-holder will work as part of a dynamic team supporting clinicians and Operational managers with a range of administrative tasks to contribute to the smooth running of the service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will co-ordinate and facilitate the dissemination of information to and from the team and be required to deal efficiently, precisely and courteously with telephone calls to and from patients, carers and health professionals. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a flexible approach and have the ability to adapt to changing priorities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a commitment to your own development and contribute to a culture of continuous improvement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we will offer:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular, meaningfulsupervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular, meaningful appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support to ensure your continuous learning and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details / informal discussion please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jo Riley, Operational Manager, Long Term Conditions, Email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;joanne.riley@mpft.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Telephone: 07812 074722&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
